    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="Kali17-kilavi">itu pakaivar tiṟai tanta nāṭu kāttaṟkup pirikiṉṟamai yuṇarntu talaivi 
            vēṟupaṭṭamai kaṇṭu tōḻi avaṉai etirppaṭṭu avaḷatu āṟṟāmaiyum iḷamaiyatarumaiyuṅ kūṟic 
            celavaḻuṅkuvittamai talai-makaṭkuk kūṟiyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">This is what the confidante, having seen the changes undergone by the heroine after realising that he had separated in order to guard the land to which the enemies brought tribute, confronting him [and] talking about her inability and the preciousness of youth, [then] told the heroine about having prevented [his] going.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="Kali17">
                <l>paṭaipaṇṇip puṉaiyavum pāmāṇṭa palavaṇaip</l>
                <l>puṭaipeyarn toṭuṅkavum puṟañcēra vuyirppavu</l>
                <l>muṭaiyatai yevaṉkoleṉ ṟūṟaḷan tavarvayi</l>
                <l>ṉaṭaicellāy naṉiyēṅki naṭuṅkaṟkā ṇaṟunutāl;</l>
                <l rend="space">tolleḻi ṟolaipiva ṭuyaruḻappat tuṟantunī</l>
                <l>valviṉai vayakkutal valittimaṉ valippaḷavai</l>
                <l>nīḷkati ravirmati niṟaivupō ṉilaiyātu</l>
                <l>nāḷiṉu nekiḻpoṭu nalaṉuṭa ṉilaiyumō;</l>
                <l rend="space">āṟṟaṉō yaṭaviva ḷaṇivāṭa vakaṉṟunī</l>
                <l>tōṟṟañcā ṟokuporuṇ muyaṟimaṉ muyalvaḷavai</l>
                <l>nāṟṟañcā ṉaḷipoykai yaṭaimutir mukaiyiṟkuk</l>
                <l>kūṟṟūḻpōṟ kuṟaipaṭūum vāḻnāḷu nilaiyumō;</l>
                <l rend="space">vakaiyeḻil vaṉappeñca varaipōka valittunī</l>
                <l>pakaiyaṟu payaviṉai muyaṟimaṉ muyalvaḷavait</l>
                <l>takaivaṇṭu putituṇṇat tātaviḻ taṇpōtiṉ</l>
                <l>mukaivāytta taṭampōlu miḷamaiyu nilaiyumō;</l>
                <l rend="space">eṉavāṅku,</l>
                <l>poruntiyāṉ ṟāṉvēṭṭa poruḷvayi ṉiṉaintacoṟ</l>
                <l>ṟiruntiya yākkaiyuṇ maruttuva ṉūṭṭiya</l>
                <l>maruntupōṉ maruntāki maṉaṉuvappap</l>
                <l>perumpeyar mīḷi peyarntaṉaṉ celavē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>            While he fashions [his] weapons in preparation, while on the many matresses glorious for [their] expanse</l>
<l>he shrinks, moving to the side, while he sighs when [you] join [his] back, </l>
<l>as you lament much as one who does not take the walk to him who mesasures</l>
<l>the obstacles, thinking “what is it [she] possesses?”, see [him] shiver, you with fragrant forehead:</l>
<l rend="space">“You, abandoning [her] while she bears the misery, [her] old grace being lost,</l>
<l>you would force strong work to shine, as a measure of firmness </l>
<l>Not lasting like the fullness of the moon shining with long rays,</l>
<l>will she last together with [her] beauty that flees, being exhausted by the day?</l>
<l rend="space">You, departing, as her adornments fade while capable pain kills [her],</l>
<l>you would strain for wealth to be gathered, worthy of an appearance, as a measure of effort.</l>
<l>Will she last [her] living days when she suffers want like at the turn of Death</l>
<l>for the maturing bud in the leaves in the vast pond abounding in fragrance?</l>
<l rend="space">You, compelling [her] to go to the limit so that [her] graceful beauty is marred in kind,</l>
<l>you would strain at beneficial work without enmity as a measure of effort.</l>
<l>Will [her] youth last that is similar to a tank in which buds flourish</l>
<l>with cool buds which open on the pollen when befitting bees eat what is new?”</l>
<l rend="space">That is to say,</l>
<l rend="space">at [my] word, in which I suitably reflected about the wealth he wanted,</l>
<l>it being a remedy like the remedy</l>
<l>that is fed by the doctor into a perfect body, </l>
<l>the strong man with a great name returned from going</l>
<l>	so that [your] mind will rejoice.</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
